# CDB List: Known malicious IPs
# Format: key:value (IP:description)
# Wazuh checks incoming events against this list for fast lookups.
#
# Usage in rules:
#   <list field="srcip" lookup="address_match_key">etc/lists/blocked-ips</list>
#
# Rebuild after editing:
#   docker exec wazuh-manager /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-control restart
#
# Sources: add IPs from threat intel feeds, incident response, etc.
# This is a starter list — maintain and update regularly.

# Example entries (uncomment and replace with your own):
# 203.0.113.50:scanner
# 198.51.100.23:bruteforce
# 192.0.2.100:c2-server
